\cf2 \cb4 \strokec2 The dose run uses\'a0
\f1 all four arms
\f0 \'a0(
\f2\fs24 \cb8 --dose-arms A B C D
\f0\fs26 \cb4 ). This means the model is pre-exposed to P\uc0\u257 \u7751 inian morphological structure before seeing English at all.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \cb4 P\uc0\u257 \u7751 inian mechanisms active during dose:
\f0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 \cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Vidyut N-hot embeddings
\f0 : each BPE token gets a 10-dim binary morpheme-boundary vector (from a heuristic over the SentencePiece vocabulary), projected via learnable\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 W: 10\uc0\u8594 768
\f0\fs26 \cb4 , summed with the token embedding. This hard-wires sub-word boundary signals.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 K\uc0\u257 raka masking
\f0 : instead of uniform random masking, tokens are assigned grammatical roles by heuristic: word-initial tokens \uc0\u8594  kart\u257  (subject, p=0.50 mask rate), derivational suffixes \u8594  vi\u347 e\u7779 a\u7751 a (adjunct, p=0.20), sub-word glue pieces \u8594  separator (p=0.10). The model sees grammatically-weighted missing tokens.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Salience recording
\f0 : during dose, per-token masking frequencies are recorded into\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 salience_weights.npy
\f0\fs26 \cb4 .\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \cb4 Stage 2 \'97 English Training (7 epochs, BabyLM strict-small)\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0 \cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Uses the standard BabyLM 10M-word English corpus\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Salience transfer
\f0 : the empirical masking frequencies from Stage 1 are loaded as a soft prior on Stage 2 masking. Tokens the model found structurally important during P\uc0\u257 \u7751 inian exposure are masked at elevated rates during English learning.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Cosine mask decay
\f0 : overall mask probability decays 0.30 \uc0\u8594  0.15 over the course of Stage 2\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Progressive sequence length
\f0 : 64 \uc0\u8594  128 \u8594  256 tokens at 0%, 40%, 75% of steps\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Muon optimizer
\f0 : Newton-Schulz orthogonalized momentum on all 2D weight matrices (attention, FFN), AdamW on 1D params and embeddings\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

