\f1\fs27\fsmilli13929 \cf5 \cb4 \strokec5 The BLiMP Score: No Fine-Tuning Involved\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \cb4 \strokec2 The\'a0
\f1 52.68% BLiMP at 8M words
\f0 \'a0is raw zero-shot, straight from the checkpoint \'97 no fine-tuning, no task-specific head, no calibration.\cb1 \
\cb4 The eval pipeline (
\f2\fs24 \cb8 official_eval.py
\f0\fs26 \cb4 ) does:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Export the\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 .pt
\f0\fs26 \cb4 \'a0checkpoint to a HuggingFace model directory\cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Run the BabyLM evaluation pipeline's\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 sentence_zero_shot
\f0\fs26 \cb4 \'a0runner with\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 --backend mlm
\f0\fs26 \cb1 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 For each BLiMP sentence pair, compute pseudo-log-likelihood (PLL) and pick the higher-scoring sentence\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 That's it \'97 no gradient update, no task head. The model scores each sentence using masked token probability, and BLiMP measures whether it assigns higher PLL to the grammatical sentence vs the ungrammatical one.\cb1 \
\cb4 52.68% at 9% of training is ~random chance + 2.68pp. This is expected \'97 the model hasn't learned much English syntax yet at 8M words. The hypothesis is that the P\uc0\u257 \u7751 inian structural prior will cause faster syntactic learning, so the curve should steepen faster than a baseline. We'll see the full-training BLiMP on\'a0
\f2\fs24 \cb8 elc.pt
\f0\fs26 \cb4 \'a0once eval completes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 the official eval is not just blimp...it has ewok, text and so many other...will it all be evaluated? where will the fine tuning be used...why the eval is focusing only on blimp\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
